Making a .pro file 
In order to do that we have to use qmake and after itâ€™s execution we will have a .pro file in out directory

debian@beaglebone:~/qtproject$ qmake -project


Adding path to the .pro file 
For this step we will use nano editor and add QT += widgets inside the file so it can be used from terminal 
debian@beaglebone:~/qtproject$ nano qtproject.pro


######################################################################
# Automatically generated by qmake (3.0) Thu Apr 8 10:00:59 2021
######################################################################

TEMPLATE = app
TARGET = qtproject
QT += widgets
INCLUDEPATH += .

# Input
SOURCES += example.cpp

